<!--
  By looking at historical data is also possible to model for each
  RIR a "low threshold" point for the RIR's unallocated address
  pool. When the RIR's unallocated address pool falls to this level it
  will request a further allocation of address blocks from IANA. The
  amount requested in this model is the lesser of 3 /8 address blocks
  and the cumulative sum of the RIR's address allocations over the
  previous 18 months. The model also assumes that the remainder of the
  address pool currently marked by the IANA as "Various" will not be
  used for further allocations until the IANA unallocated pool is
  exhausted.  This overall model is indicated in Figure 30.  This is
