  <p>

  These individual RIR pool behaviours can be summed, as shown in
  Figure 31. Each upward movement in the RIR Pool series represents
  an IANA allocation to one of the RIRs, while the downward movement
  represents the cumulative address allocation rate across the RIR
  system.

  </p><p class="outdent">
  <a href="./fig29g.png" ><IMG src="./fig29g.png" width="90%"></a><BR>
